  levelNumber: 8
  levelName: Muyil
  location: Quintana Roo, Mexico
  levelDescription: "Muyil, settled early and continuously occupied into the Postclassic,
    served as a strategic hub for coastal and inland trade along the eastern Yucat\xE1n.
    Connected to the Sian Ka\u2019an lagoon system, its canals allowed canoe traffic
    to move salt, obsidian, honey, shell, textiles, and ritual goods along major
    maritime routes. Architecturally, Muyil blends Pet\xE9n-style temple forms with
    local Caribbean elements, reflecting centuries of cultural exchange. Its temples
    overlook a landscape shaped as much by commerce as by ceremony, revealing the
    importance of water-borne trade to Maya economies.\n\nFrom forest to sea, goods
    and ideas flowed through Muyil\u2019s watery corridors."
